msgstr ""

msgid "How it works - Ski Parrainage"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Finding a partner for the 4 Vallées Ambassador Offer usually means "
"scrambling in the Facebook group and hoping the person you find doesn't "
"disappear before you can meet. This service does the matchmaking - you "
"register, and we pair you with a partner. After that it's over to you and "
"the standard Téléverbier application process. This page shows the end-to-end "
"process."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Start by choosing the role that fits you. You're an Ambassador if you held a "
"4 Vallées seasonal or annual pass in one of the previous two seasons and "
"want to refer a new holder. You're a Referee if you're new to the 4 Vallées "
"and need an Ambassador to refer you. You register in one role, and you only "
"ever have one registration."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"You must confirm your email address before your registration is active. "
"We'll email you a verification link when you register. Once you've clicked "
"the link you're active and in the queue - there's nothing else you need to "
"do."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"As soon as a suitable partner is available, the system pairs you - one "
"Ambassador with one Referee. You don't browse or choose; we assign a partner "
"and email you both. If there are people waiting for a match with your role "
"(e.g. you register as a Referee, and there are Ambassadors waiting) the "
"match will be instant."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"From that moment a contact window starts - its length is shown in the match "
"email. During it, you can see your match partner's first name, but not their "
"email or phone number. Those contact details stay hidden until you have both "
"accepted. This is deliberate: it's the core privacy promise of the service."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Both of you need to accept within the contact window. If your partner "
"accepts first, you'll see the match waiting on you; once you accept too, "
"you're through to the final step. Accepting simply means you're happy to go "
"ahead and share your contact details with each other."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"If you decline, or the window runs out before you respond, the match ends "
"and you're taken out of the queue for the moment - but nothing is lost. Your "
"registration is kept, and you can rejoin from your account page whenever "
"you're ready. The partner who did accept goes back to the front of the "
"queue, so they're matched again quickly."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Once you've both accepted, we reveal each other's contact details - and only "
"then. That's the finish line for us: you can now get in touch and go make "
"your application together. Filling in the form and buying your passes "
"happens off the app, directly with the ticket office."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"If your partner arranges to meet and then doesn't show up, you can report "
"it. We trust the report straight away: you go back to the front of the queue "
"to be paired again, and the person who didn't show is removed from the pool."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"A match falling through is normal and it doesn't set you back: unless you "
"were the one who dropped out, you return to the front of the queue and are "
"matched again. Over a season you might be part of several matches before one "
"sticks."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Changed your mind? You can leave the programme at any time, and register "
"again later if you want to come back."
msgstr ""

